  <h2>Problem statement</h2>
  <p>Researchers want to share project data with colleagues outside of dscout.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="getting-started-with-share-links">Getting started with share links</h2>
<p>Generated links live inside the project link manager on the project home page.</p>

<p>The interface below shows the link manager call-to-action on the right column.</p>

<figure>
	<img src="/assets/images/public-share-links-1.png" title="Public share links - Project link manager call to action" />
	<figcaption class="media-caption center">Public share links - Project link manager call to action</figcaption>
</figure>

<p>The project link manager is a table of links generated and shared. Researchers can navigate to links via the manager and edit link settings.</p>

<figure>
	<img src="/assets/images/public-share-links-2.png" title="Public share links - Project link manager" />
	<figcaption class="media-caption center">Public share links - Project link manager</figcaption>
</figure>

<p>Inside a linkâ€™s settings are features:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Delete the share link</li>
  <li>Set an access code for people to access the content behind the link</li>
  <li>Set link expiration</li>
  <li>Share link to chosen Slack channels</li>
</ul>

<figure>
	<img src="/assets/images/public-share-links-3.png" title="Public share links - Share link modal while sharing link" />
	<figcaption class="media-caption center">Public share links - Share link modal while sharing link</figcaption>
</figure>

<h2 id="creating-a-link">Creating a link</h2>

<p>Once a researcher finds a media that they want to share, they click on the sharing button on the media. Following, theyâ€™re greeted with the sharing modal below.</p>

<p>The first step to sharing media is to click on â€œGenerate public share link.â€</p>

